      "label": "Revive MemPalace After Compact",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "CLAUDE.md",
      "source_location": "### Revive MemPalace after every compact",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "The MemPalace MCP server (stdio) drops silently across long sessions and every /compact boundary; tools show as disconnected with no error and no data loss (palace and mempalace.yaml stay intact). After every /compact, verify connection and prompt the user to run /plugin or /mcp to revive it (the agent cannot invoke slash-commands itself). Until reconnected, fall back to file memory plus Graphify.",
      "id": "claude_mempalace_revival_after_compact",
      "community": 1,
      "norm_label": "revive mempalace after compact"
    },
    {
      "label": "Working Style",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "CLAUDE.md",
      "source_location": "## Working Style",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Implementation tasks: identify the smallest relevant file set, explain the intended change briefly, make focused edits, run the narrowest useful test, avoid unnecessary rewrites. Design tasks: use Graphify for repo structure, MemPalace for past decisions only if relevant, keep answers concise and action-oriented.",
      "id": "claude_working_style",
      "community": 2,
      "norm_label": "working style"
    },
    {
      "label": "Low-Token High-Signal Project Rule",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "CLAUDE.md",
      "source_location": "## Project Rule",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Optimize for low-token, high-signal work. Prefer precise context retrieval over loading large files or repeating architecture summaries. This is the overarching design intent behind the token usage, Graphify, and MemPalace policies.",
      "id": "claude_project_rule",
      "community": 2,
      "norm_label": "low-token high-signal project rule"
    },
